curvature condition (138) into ∇⊥(K⊥1 − K⊥2 ) = 2w/Ä∇ , and these new boundary terms matter in order to arrive at this result (Deserno

et al., 2007).

Furthermore, the framework can also be applied to any ﬁelds

deﬁned on the curved geometry, not just the geometry itself.

